radiographic_examinations.findings: No free air detected beneath the diaphragms. Gas is seen in non-dilated loops of the ascending, transverse, and descending colon, with probable gas and stool in the rectum. A single loop of bowel in the right upper quadrant measures 9.1 cm in diameter and appears to represent a focally dilated loop of small bowel. The upright view shows fluid levels in this dilated loop and in scattered other loops. No other dilated air-filled loops of small or large bowel are identified. No bowel wall thickening is detected. Multiple surgical clips as well as two ring-like clips are seen in the upper abdomen. Incidental note is made of an IUD.
